{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# op-cert deploy blockers (Dockerfile.opcert + nginx guard map)\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Run the 76d2 box deploy on the Gerrit host (compose-up / `docker compose up -d --build opcert` + nginx render of rebar.conf.template).\n\n## Expected\nThe opcert container builds and the nginx /opcert/ route loads.\n\n## Actual\n- Docker build fails: `ssh-keygen -V` (validity-interval flag) errors -> empty version -> 'ERROR: OpenSSH >= 8.9 is required'.\n- nginx -t fails: 'could not build map_hash, you should increase map_hash_bucket_size: 64' (48-char guard token overflows default bucket).\n(Deploy fail-safe worked: nginx rolled back, Gerrit unaffected.)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] infra/compose/Dockerfile.opcert reads the OpenSSH version from `ssh -V` (not `ssh-keygen -V`); a test asserts this.\n- [ ] infra/nginx/rebar.conf.template sets `map_hash_bucket_size` before the guard map; a test asserts this.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] the box deploy succeeds after the fix: opcert container up, nginx /opcert/ route loads, Gerrit unaffected."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784080375660152001,"uuid":"da9eb226-1fb8-4bfb-8e96-c1741cbf4173"}